place.name: SWARBY
place.gazetteerText: SWARBY, a parish in Sleaford district, Lincoln; 3¾ miles SSW of Sleaford r. station. Post town, Sleaford. Acres, 910. Real property, £1,406. Pop., 188. houses, 39. The manor belongs to T. Whichcote, Bart. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £60. Patron, Sir T. Whichcote, Bart. The church was repaired in 1855. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
